sql:
SELECT job_title
FROM job_positions
WHERE id = 1;

SELECT AVG(salary) AS average_salary
FROM job_positions
WHERE job_title = 'Software Engineer';

SELECT company_size, COUNT(*) AS num_jobs
FROM job_positions
GROUP BY company_size;

SELECT job_title
FROM job_positions
WHERE salary > (SELECT AVG(salary) FROM job_positions);

external_knowledge:
- Purchasing power is often measured by the ratio of salary to cost of living; 
- A higher ratio typically indicates a higher standard of living; 
- In this context, 'Silicon Valley' refers to a specific tech hub in the San Francisco Bay Area, known for its high cost of living and high-paying tech jobs.

